  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "I understand wanting to tailor your Quora feed to better match your interests. To reduce or block content related to Donald Trump on your Quora feed, you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Unfollow Relevant Topics**\nIf you're following topics related to politics or specifically about Donald Trump, unfollowing them can significantly reduce related content.\n\n- **On Desktop:**\n  1. Go to [Quora](https://www.quora.com/) and log in to your account.\n  2. Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner and select **\"Following\"** from the dropdown menu.\n  3. Browse through your followed topics and click the **\"Unfollow\"** button next to any topics related to politics, government, or Donald Trump.\n\n- **On Mobile:**\n  1. Open the Quora app and log in.\n  2. Tap on your profile picture and go to **\"Following.\"**\n  3. Find and unfollow relevant topics as mentioned above.\n\n### 2. **Hide Specific Questions or Answers**\nIf certain questions or answers about Donald Trump still appear in your feed, you can hide them to prevent similar content from showing up.\n\n- **To Hide a Question:**\n  1. Locate the question about Donald Trump in your feed.\n  2. Click on the three-dot menu (**\u22ef**) next to the question.\n  3. Select **\"Hide question\"** or **\"Don\u2019t show similar questions.\"**\n\n- **To Hide an Answer:**\n  1. Find the answer related to Donald Trump.\n  2. Click on the three-dot menu (**\u22ef**) next to the answer.\n  3. Choose **\"Hide answer\"** or **\"Don\u2019t show similar answers.\"**\n\n### 3. **Adjust Your Interests**\nRegularly updating your interests ensures that your feed remains relevant to your preferences.\n\n1. **On Desktop:**\n   - Go to your profile by clicking your profile picture.\n   - Click on **\"Interests.\"**\n   - Review and remove any interests related to politics or Donald Trump.\n\n2. **On Mobile:**\n   - Navigate to your profile.\n   - Tap on **\"Interests.\"**\n   - Edit your interests accordingly.\n\n### 4. **Block Specific Users**\nIf certain users frequently post content about Donald Trump and it's bothering you, consider blocking them.\n\n1. Visit the user\u2019s profile you want to block.\n2. Click on the three-dot menu (**\u22ef**) on their profile.\n3. Select **\"Block\"** from the options.\n\n### 5. **Use the \"Don't Show\" Feature**\nQuora often provides options to refine what you see based on your interactions.\n\n- When you hide a question or answer, look for options like **\"Don't show similar posts.\"** Selecting this helps Quora learn your preferences better.\n\n### 6. **Provide Feedback to Quora**\nIf you continue to see unwanted content despite these efforts, consider providing feedback to Quora.\n\n1. Scroll to the bottom of the Quora page.\n2. Click on **\"Contact Us\"** or **\"Help\"**.\n3. Submit a request explaining your issue with unwanted content about Donald Trump.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Regularly Review Your Feed:** Periodically check the topics and users you follow to ensure they still align with your interests.\n  \n- **Engage with Preferred Content:** By interacting more with the content you enjoy (upvoting, following topics/users), Quora's algorithm will better understand your preferences and tailor your feed accordingly.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to minimize or eliminate content related to Donald Trump from your Quora feed, making your experience more enjoyable and aligned with your interests.\n\nIf you need more detailed assistance, you can visit Quora's [Help Center](https://help.quora.com/) for additional support.",
